---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    <strong>read-the-syspapers</strong> is a personal, agent-assisted reading log for systems
    top-conference papers. Each summary is a structured, PhD-depth write-up: problem, key
    insight, design, evaluation, novelty, limitations, related work.
  </p>
  <p>
    Summaries are produced by coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, Cursor, Aider) driven
    by the shared harness in <code>AGENTS.md</code> and <code>prompts/</code>. Every summary
    records which agent produced it in the <code>written_by</code> frontmatter field, so you
    can compare how different agents handle the same paper.
  </p>
  <p>
    The stack is Astro + content collections + Pagefind, deployed to GitHub Pages.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
